NPM - Package Manager

Hands on 1 : 
-------------------

npm init
npm_package // (after this press enter multiple times till the line "is itok?(yes)"give yes and press enter)
npm install react
npm install lodash@4.17.0 --save
npm install redux@4 --save
npm install mocha --save-dev
npm install eslint@6 --save-dev

//(run the test)

----------------------------------------------------
Hands on 2 : 

npm init
npm_commands //(after this press enter multiple times till the line "is it ok?(yes)" give yes and press enter)
create index.js in root of folder
Open index.js file and add below code and save

	[
		var myVar="node package manager".toUpperCase();
		console.log(myVar);
	]

Open package.json
Go to script section and add below

"release":"npm -v && node -v", 
"build":"node index.js"
 
run in terminal : npm run release|tee output1.txt 
run in terminal :  npm run build|tee output.txt

//(run the test)

